params.amountIn: The maximum amount of collateral tokens to spend
params.fundingManager: The funding manager to buy from
params.minAmountOut: The minimum amount of issuance tokens to receive
params.recipient: The address to receive the purchased tokens

params.authorizerConfig: The config data for the orchestrator's {IAuthorizer_v1} instance.
params.fundingManagerConfig: The config data for the orchestrator's {IFundingManager_v1} instance.
params.issuanceTokenParams: The issuance token's parameters (name, symbol, decimals, maxSupply).
params.migrationConfig_: The config data for the migration.
params.moduleConfigs: Variable length set of optional module's config data.
params.paymentProcessorConfig: The config data for the orchestrator's {IPaymentProcessor_v1} instance.

returns._0: CreatedOrchestrator Returns the created orchestrator instance.
isGraduated Whether the issuance token has been graduated
isImmutable Whether the issuance token is immutable

isTrustedForwarder(address).details: Indicates whether any particular address is the trusted forwarder.

params.amountIn: The amount of issuance tokens to sell
params.fundingManager: The funding manager to sell to
params.minAmountOut: The minimum amount of collateral tokens to receive
params.recipient: The address to receive the purchased tokens

trustedForwarder().details: Returns the address of the trusted forwarder.

buyFor(address,address,uint256,uint256).notice: Buys tokens from the bonding curve funding manager for a recipient

createPIMWorkflow((bool,address),((uint2.notice: Deploys a new issuance token and uses that to deploy a workflow with restricted bonding curve.

getIsGraduated(address).notice: Returns whether the issuance token has been graduated

getIsImmutable(address).notice: Returns whether the issuance token is immutable

sellTo(address,address,uint256,uint256).notice: Sells tokens to the funding manager for a recipient
